N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 12 ยง 285.9 - Suspension of rules

State Regulations

In particular cases where, in the discretion of the

Industrial Commissioner, such procedure is deemed warranted, any of these rules
may be suspended or abrogated, and for each particular case the Industrial

Commissioner may issue such further rules as the circumstances
warrant. Notes
